# CVE-2026-33671 — picomatch 4.0.3 ReDoS.
# Present ONLY in the npm CLI bundled with the node:22-slim base image
# (/usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/node_modules/picomatch), not in our app deps
# (we pin picomatch >=4.0.4 via package.json overrides). npm is not invoked at
# runtime — the production image runs `node dist/src/main.js` — so this code path
# is not reachable. Will clear when the base image ships a patched npm.
CVE-2026-33671

# CVE-2026-48815 — @sigstore/* certificateOIDs verification bypass.
# Same situation as above: present ONLY in the npm CLI bundled with the
# node:22-slim base image (/usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/node_modules/@sigstore),
# not in our app deps (our lockfile has no sigstore). npm's package-provenance
# verification is not invoked at runtime, so this code path is not reachable.
# Will clear when the base image ships a patched npm.
CVE-2026-48815
